42 SECTION 7. Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, the Secretary of
43 Health and Human Services or a designee, in conjunction with the Division of Medical
44 Assistance, shall establish a regional pilot program to increase the capacity of staffed long-term
45 care beds, beds for patients with dementia diagnoses, and beds for geriatric patients with
46 psychiatric diagnoses in the state’s nursing facilities; provided, that the pilot may review the
47 prior temporary program that added short-term rehabilitation capacity in all regions of
